            <title>[GROOVY-5036] Date and Calendar JSON serialization yields stackoverflow errors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5036</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Date and Calendar contain references to themselves, and the standard object properties serialization logic tries to serialize an infinite chains of such references, yielding a stack overflow error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The idea is to serialize those dates and calendars into ISO-8601 compliant date strings, that are also parseable from JavaScript with Date.parse(...).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
